The Federal Executive Council on Wednesday approved over sixteen-billion naira for various ecological and flood control projects, which were earlier, proposed for the 3rd and 4th quarters of 2020.  The Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina briefing State House Correspondents after FEC meeting, said that the projects include bridges, road improvement and gully erosion control works to be executed in Abia, Ogun, Imo, Osun, Adamawa, Cross Rivers, Gombe, Taraba, Katsina, Kwara, Niger and Jigawa states as well as the FCT.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that Mr Adesina added that Council equally approved the revised estimate for the construction of Damaturu-Gasua-Nguru 132 KVA Double Circuit Transmission Line for Transmission Company of Nigeria (TCN).  On his part, Minister of Transportation, Rotimi Amaechi said FEC approved over 17billion naira for the purchase of Canty Towers, on Victoria Island, Lagos, to serve as the new headquarters of Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency, (NIMASA), the amount is inclusive of 7.5% tax.